#+TITLE: Really Fun Problem
#+AUTHOR: Daniel

* Problem
Factorize x^2 - y^2 + 2yz - z^2.

* First Step
The back half of the expression is -( y^2 - 2yz + z^2), which goes to (y - z)(y - z).

* Second Step
Now you have x^2 - (y - z)^2, so you can do the difference of two squares thing.

Now you have (x + y - z)(x - y - z).
